info.title: Wsf Fares API
info.description: Wsf Fares API - Washington State Department of Transportation APIs

Description.description: Human-readable description of the roadway location, such as interchange names or cross streets.

Direction.description: Traffic direction designation: N, S, B, NB, or SB, indicating which side of the highway is affected.

Latitude.description: Latitude of the roadway location in decimal degrees.

Longitude.description: Longitude of the roadway location in decimal degrees.

MilePost.description: Milepost marker along the highway corridor, with 0 indicating route terminus.

RoadName.description: Highway or route designation code, such as '005' for I-5 or '090' for I-90.

RoadwayLocation.description: Roadway location information including route, milepost, coordinates, and direction.

FetchCacheFlushDateFaresOutput.description: UTC datetime when static endpoint data was last updated, or undefined if no update has occurred.

DateFrom.description: UTC datetime when data becomes available (earliest valid trip date).

DateThru.description: UTC datetime when data stops being available (latest valid trip date).

FetchFaresValidDateRangeOutput.description: Date range for which fares data is currently published and available.

DepartingDescription.description: Display name of the departing terminal, or null if unavailable.

ArrivingDescription.description: Display name of the arriving terminal, or null if unavailable.

CollectionDescription.description: Text description of fare collection procedures for this terminal combination, or null if unavailable.

FetchTerminalComboFaresOutput.description: Fare collection description for a terminal combination with terminal names and collection procedures.

DepartingTerminalID.description: Numeric ID of the departing terminal.

DepartingDescription.description: Display name of the departing terminal, or null if unavailable.

ArrivingTerminalID.description: Numeric ID of the arriving terminal.

ArrivingDescription.description: Display name of the arriving terminal, or null if unavailable.

CollectionDescription.description: Text description of fare collection procedures for this terminal combination, or null if unavailable.

items.description: Fare collection description for a terminal combination with IDs, names, and collection procedures.

TerminalComboVerbose.description: Array of terminal combination information for the trip date.

TerminalComboIndex.description: Array index of terminal combination in TerminalComboVerbose array.

LineItemIndex.description: Array index of one-way fare line items in LineItems array.

RoundTripLineItemIndex.description: Array index of round trip fare line items in RoundTripLineItems array.

items.description: Cross-reference mapping between terminal combinations and fare line item arrays.

LineItemLookup.description: Array of cross-reference mappings between terminal combinations and fare line items.

FareLineItemID.description: Numeric ID of the fare line item.

FareLineItem.description: Display name of the fare line item, or null if unavailable.

Category.description: Category grouping for the fare (e.g., 'Passenger', 'Vehicle'), or null if unavailable.

DirectionIndependent.description: True if fare amount is the same regardless of departure direction, false if it varies by terminal.

items.description: Fare line item with identifier, description, category, direction independence, and cost.

LineItems.description: Array of one-way fare line item arrays, one per terminal combination.

FareLineItemID.description: Numeric ID of the fare line item.

FareLineItem.description: Display name of the fare line item, or null if unavailable.

Category.description: Category grouping for the fare (e.g., 'Passenger', 'Vehicle'), or null if unavailable.

DirectionIndependent.description: True if fare amount is the same regardless of departure direction, false if it varies by terminal.

items.description: Fare line item with identifier, description, category, direction independence, and cost.

RoundTripLineItems.description: Array of round trip fare line item arrays, one per terminal combination.

FetchFareLineItemsVerboseOutput.description: Comprehensive fare line item data for all terminal combinations on a trip date.

get.summary: List all fare line items for a specific terminal combination and trip type.

FareLineItemID.description: Numeric ID of the fare line item.

FareLineItem.description: Display name of the fare line item, or null if unavailable.

Category.description: Category grouping for the fare (e.g., 'Passenger', 'Vehicle'), or null if unavailable.

DirectionIndependent.description: True if fare amount is the same regardless of departure direction, false if it varies by terminal.

items.description: Fare line item with identifier, description, category, direction independence, and cost.

sampleResponse.description: Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 23 total)

get.summary: Calculate fare totals for a terminal combination with selected line items and quantities.

TotalType.description: Code indicating total type: 1 = Departing, 2 = Return, 3 = Either (direction independent), 4 = Grand Total.

Description.description: Display name of the fare total (e.g., 'Anacortes to Friday Harbor', 'Grand Total'), or null if unavailable.

BriefDescription.description: Short string representation of total type (e.g., 'Depart', 'Either', 'Total'), or null if unavailable.

Amount.description: Total fare amount in dollars for this total type.

items.description: Fare total breakdown with type, description, and amount.

sampleResponse.description: Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 3 total)

tags.name: cache-flush-date-fares
tags.description: Cache invalidation timestamp for static WSF fares data.
tags.x-description: Returns the UTC datetime when static endpoint data for the wsf-fares API was last updated. Use this endpoint to determine when to invalidate cached fares information.
x-useCases: Poll periodically to detect when static fares data has changed.
Invalidate application cache when the returned date changes.
Coordinate cache refresh across multiple static endpoints.

tags.name: valid-date-range
tags.description: Validity period for published WSF fare data.
tags.x-description: Returns the start and end dates between which fare information is accurate and available for all ferry routes. Use the cacheFlushDate endpoint for this API to determine when to invalidate cached data for this group.
x-useCases: Determine valid trip dates for fare queries.
Validate trip date inputs before calling other endpoints.
Display available date ranges in booking interfaces.

tags.name: terminals
tags.description: WSF terminal facilities serving as departure and arrival points for ferry routes.
tags.x-description: Terminals represent port facilities with unique identifiers and names. Use the cacheFlushDate endpoint for this API to determine when to invalidate cached data for this group.
x-useCases: Display terminal options for trip planning interfaces.
Determine valid terminal pairs for route selection.
Build terminal lookup and navigation features.

tags.name: terminal-combo
tags.description: Valid terminal pairings with fare collection procedures for WSF routes.
tags.x-description: Terminal combinations define which terminals are connected and describe where and how fares are collected for each route. Use the cacheFlushDate endpoint for this API to determine when to invalidate cached data for this group.
x-useCases: Determine route availability between terminal pairs.
Understand fare collection procedures for specific routes.
Build journey planning interfaces with fare collection details.

tags.name: fare-line-items
tags.description: Individual fare components for WSF routes by passenger and vehicle types.
tags.x-description: Fare line items represent pricing components for different passenger categories, vehicle types, and route combinations. Use the cacheFlushDate endpoint for this API to determine when to invalidate cached data for this group.
x-useCases: Display fare options for different passenger and vehicle types.
Calculate journey costs based on route and demographics.
Build fare selection interfaces for ticket purchasing.

tags.name: fare-totals
tags.description: Calculated fare totals for WSF journeys by selected line items and quantities.
tags.x-description: Fare totals combine individual fare line items with quantities to provide complete pricing breakdowns including departing, return, direction-independent, and grand totals. Use the cacheFlushDate endpoint for this API to determine when to invalidate cached data for this group.
x-useCases: Calculate complete journey costs for ticket pricing.
Display fare breakdowns by leg and total amount.
Process payment amounts for ferry trips.
